{"title": "Defeat Means Respect", "content": "Bill the Butcher, Gangs of New York \"The finest beating I ever took. My face was pulp. My guts pierced. My ribs messed up. When he came to finish me, I couldn't look him in the eye. He spared me, because he wanted me to live in shame. This was a great man. A great man. So I cut out the eye that looked away \u2014 sent it to him wrapped in blue paper.\"\n\nA villain spends his whole first appearance insulting or belittling his opponents. After a humiliating defeat at the hands of The Hero he starts to become nicer to those who have won and now considers them to be a Worthy Opponent. Sometimes it may take repeated losses to cause this in the case of a particularly stubborn villain.\n\nEvery Unknown Rival is motivated by this trope. This is also the idea behind the victims of The Bully: \"You have to stand for yourself\".\n\nDistinct from Defeat Means Friendship because the opponent is still an enemy to the victor, but it can eventually evolve into friendship. Compare Graceful Loser and Touch\u00e9.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DefeatMeansRespect", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GangsOfNewYork", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/TengenToppaGurrenLagann", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/RomeoXJuliet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/TenchiMuyo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/YoureUnderArrest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SoulEater", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FistOfTheNorthStar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PokemonKyuremVSTheSwordOfJustice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MakenKi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/VariableGeo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/YuGiOh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MissKobayashisDragonMaid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/HajimeNoIppo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TalladegaNightsTheBalladOfRickyBobby", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheKarateKid1984", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/JourneyToChaos", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/